[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    113[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    114[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mSuggested fix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Add a note in Step 2 or the performance section: "EHR API latency dominates the pipeline. If your FHIR server responds in 200-500ms per call, sequential queries work within the latency budget. If response times are higher, parallelize the FHIR queries or maintain a pre-fetched patient context cache (refreshed on clinical events) to keep end-to-end latency under 5 seconds."[K
