[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    136[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe problem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The prerequisites list VPC endpoints for Bedrock, S3, DynamoDB, and CloudWatch Logs. KMS is not listed. If S3 uses SSE-KMS (as specified in the Encryption row), every S3 GetObject call to load prompt templates requires a KMS API call to decrypt the data key. Without a KMS VPC endpoint, Lambda in a private subnet cannot reach KMS and will fail with timeout or access errors when loading prompts from S3.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    137[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    138[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mSuggested fix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Add [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcom.amazonaws.{region}.kms[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m (interface endpoint) to the VPC endpoint list. This is the same issue flagged in Recipe 1.3's review and should be consistently addressed across all recipes that use SSE-KMS with Lambda in a VPC.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    139[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
