[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    152[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe problem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The architecture shows Lambda calling an "EHR API / FHIR Server" for patient context. If this is an external API (e.g., Epic's FHIR endpoint hosted outside your VPC), Lambda in a private subnet needs an egress path: either a NAT Gateway or a specific VPC endpoint if the EHR offers PrivateLink. If the EHR is internal (within the same VPC or peered VPC), this is fine. The recipe doesn't clarify which scenario applies or how to handle external EHR APIs.[K
